 2\sin(x)\cos(x)=\tan(x) 
\sin(x) = 0 \implies x \in \{ 0, \pi, 2\pi\}
 2\cos(x)=\frac 1{\cos x} \iff \cos^2 x = \frac 12 \iff x \in \left\{ \frac \pi 4, \frac {3\pi} 4, \frac {5\pi} 4, \frac {7\pi} 4 \right\}  
\tan{(x)}=\frac{\sin (x)}{\cos(x)}
 2\sin{(x)}\cos{(x)}=\frac{\sin{(x)}}{\cos(x)} 
 \sin{(x)}(2\cos^2(x)-1) =0
 \sin(x)=0 \;\;\; \text{ and } \;\;\; 2\cos^2(x)-1=0 
2\sin x\cos x=\dfrac{\sin x}{\cos x}\\ \implies \cos x=\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\text{ and/or }\sin x=0\\ \implies x=\dfrac{\pi}{4},\dfrac{3\pi}{4},\dfrac{5\pi}{4},\dfrac{7\pi}{4},0,\pi,2\pi
